dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.cbe.tip.fmk.CommonObjectInfo
dataStructure.description:
This object class defines the common attributes for all addressable object classes used in the MTOSI/MTNM interface. This class should merge up into its parent class. There is currently no merge-up stereotype to direct the implementation so the class has not been decorated.

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: CommonObjectInfo

child.name: namingOsRef
child.description:
This attribute represents an identifier for the steward of the object. See R_TMF518_FMW_I_0001.This attribute represents an identifier for the steward of the object, intended as the OS that sets the name of the object. The namingOS attribute is set by the OS that is responsible for setting the "name" of the object.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC disabled
child.label: namingOsRef

child.name: discoveredName
child.description:
This attribute contains the name of the object when its existence is first published on the CCV. See R_TMF518_FMW_I_0001 and R_TMF518_FMW_I_0003.This attribute contains the name of the object when its existence is first published on the CCV but only in the case where the OS that publishes the object on the CCV is not the naming OS.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is invariant

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC disabled
child.label: discoveredName

child.name: userLabel
child.description:
This attribute represents a provisionable, user friendly name for the object. The userLabel attribute is owned and may be set by the requesting OS or the naming OS. The difference between the userLabel and the name is that the userLabel is an attribute of the object that may be "set" by the requesting OS or the naming OS. This attribute may be unique amongst all instances of this object in the target OS.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional

This attribute is AVC enabled
child.label: userLabel
